oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Tah-Chee, or Dutch, a Cherokee Chief, wearing a tunic with a knife tucked into the belt around his waist.
Tah-Chee (1790-1848), also known as 'Dutch' or 'Captain William Dutch', was a Cherokee leader. In 1835, he served as an Indian representative at the signing of the Camp Homes peace treaty.
